[Minimal details are given about the circumstances that led to the deaths of 3 out of 4 Americans staying at a beach resort in the Bahamas. The 2 couples were staying in 2 separate "villas"; not stated is how the 2 "villas" are situated in relation to each other. Some of the 4 people had been sick for at least 2 days with nausea and vomiting, seeking care at a local medical facility. No further details are given, other than the police saying that 2 may have convulsed prior to death. At this point, there is insufficient information to speculate on the cause of this illness in these 4 resort guests, although another hotel guest speculated that leaking air conditioner coolant may have been at fault. More information on this outbreak would be appreciated from knowledgeable sources.

The Bahamas, a sovereign country in the West Indies in the Atlantic, consists of more than 3000 islands. It is located north of Cuba and southeast of the US state of Florida (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Bahamas). The capital, Nassau, is on the island of New Providence. Exuma is a district of The Bahamas, consisting of several hundred islands, the largest of which is Great Exuma (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exuma). A map showing the location of Grand Exuma can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Nassau,+The+Bahamas/Grand+Isle+Resort+And+Residences,+Great+Exuma,+Bahamas. - Mod.ML

